cast, like the broken golem, orc pawns, that annoying rouge in the arena etc.  It would increase our mana pool in a way, but having it only work on casting mobs would make it not-so overpowered.  <br>
<br>
Another possiblity would be to have it as a skill (like most wizards want harvast to be)  increasing your chances at gaining mana back, and more mana for a higher skill. <br>
<br>
tell me what you think. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uspace78.showPublicProfile?language=EN>space78</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 36<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/7/01 8:58 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Possible spell line - mana syphon (*sp?)</span><hr size=1> ive always wanted a spell like this, wouldnt really help us solo, its been awhile since i was able to succesfully solo a caster mob without coming near death.<br>
<br>
personally i would love to see a super &quot;med&quot;  ever since lvl 35 we don't have to look at the book anymore. what if they made it where we med twice as fast when we look at the book, and made it where we would be unaware of everything, i mean EVERYTHING like our roots breaking, the only thing that would get our attention would be a mob smacking us, and that could have the potential to break us up so badly we could actually loose some mana <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umitebe123.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MiteBe123</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/7/01 7:21 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Possible spell line - mana syphon (*sp?)</span><hr size=1> I have thought of something like this too but this type of spell is already in the enchanter realm with ToT (if I understood your post correctly) and we know how Verant doesnt like to blur class lines (/sarcasm off) <br>
<br>
Anyhoo, my idea is similar but its a buff ( I know sue me I dont want buffs either but hear me out) that acts as a kinda reverse damage shield against spells. To refine this thought more closely. It would be cast on group members like a damage shield and a certain percentage/amout of spell damage would be reduced from the group members damage and converted to mana for the lucky wizard. I does 3 things, improves our groupability, gets us more mana and isnt all that good for soloing because it would only be cost effective if you had say 3 others in your group. Kinda a reverse damage shield and mana seive all in one. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umitebe123.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MiteBe123</A> at: 5/7/01 6:08:31 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ucattheinvoker.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cat the Invoker</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/8/01 4:45 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> we are teleporter only</span><hr size=1> No, they wont even consider to give this kind of spell to wizard.<br>
